## Tasks

Tasks describe what must be achieved and how to verify it — not which functions to call.

| ID | Description | Files | Schedule | Acceptance |
|----|-------------|-------|----------|------------|
| 1 | [what to achieve] | `src/renderer/foo.cpp` | GATE | [observable result] |
| 2 | [what to achieve] | `src/game/bar.cpp` | ‖ | [observable result] |
| 3 | [what to achieve] | `src/game/baz.cpp` | ‖ with 2 | [observable result] |
| 4 | [what to achieve] | `shaders/game/new.glsl` | → | sokol-shdc compiles cleanly |
| 5 | [what to achieve] | `src/renderer/renderer.cpp` | → | cmake exits 0; [behavior visible] |

**Schedule codes**:
- `GATE` — runs alone first; everything after depends on it
- `‖` — parallel with adjacent `‖` tasks; listed Files must be disjoint
- `→` — sequential, runs after all preceding tasks (or after the last GATE)

